<TITLE> Poet Nirmalendu Gun turns 65 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Netrokona, June 22 (bdnews24.com)The 65th birthday of poet Nirmalendu Gun was observed by his fans across the country on Sunday. Celebrations were held in his ancestral village of Kashbon in Barhatta Upazila. The popular poet arrived in his ancestral village on Saturday to be present through all the festivities. The day's activities marked their start at 7am with the poet planting a 'bakul' tree in his village home in Kashbon. A literary morning was organised at 9am at the poet's place, where poetry and prose recitations took place. At Barhatta Upazila Parishad auditorium at 3pm started a discussion session chaired by the anniversary observance Parishad president Girindra Sarkar. The assembly also gave away Nirmalendu Gun birth anniversary prizes to meritorious and successful students. Gun told his fans and well wishers, "My stature was reduced as I was born as a baby. Now as I advance towards death, I'm growing bigger and bigger." 
